16
00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:38.940
Oh my God!

17
00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:02.700
What do you want. sir?
A cigarette or a betel-leaf?

18
00:03:03.340 --> 00:03:06.140
I want a life. - Life..?

19
00:03:06.220 --> 00:03:09.940
Not yours. Madhav Singh's life.
- Madhav Singh's..?

20
00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:12.220
Yes! Madhav Singh's life!

21
00:03:14.660 --> 00:03:16.180
Where is the rat?

22
00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:29.140
Are they coming towards
me or going elsewhere?

23
00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:32.660
Well? Can't you see anymore?
- What did you say?

24
00:03:32.740 --> 00:03:37.380
So you can't hear me either?
You're dead. blind and deaf!

25
00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:41.700
Scared? When I can't see a thing.
whom will I be scared of?

26
00:03:42.660 --> 00:03:43.740
I'll deal with them.

27
00:03:45.420 --> 00:03:49.860
Problem with my eyes.
I suddenly stop seeing things.

28
00:03:49.940 --> 00:03:53.780
And problem with my ears.
I'm suddenly hard of hearing.

29
00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:56.580
So when must I put on my hearing-aid..

30
00:03:56.660 --> 00:03:58.820
..and when must I
put on the glasses..?

31
00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:01.900
It all has to do with timing. you see.

32
00:04:12.900 --> 00:04:15.100
Madhav Singh!

33
00:04:28.420 --> 00:04:31.100
Suraj.. Suraj.

34
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:36.300
Death hovers above my head.

35
00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:41.660
Not your head? Krupa.
It stands before them.

36
00:04:42.140 --> 00:04:46.940
Dressed in a suit.
you want to play a thug. mister?

37
00:05:02.980 --> 00:05:07.260
Is it okay now. Madhav Singh?
- You're not mad. are you?

38
00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:11.660
Aren't you scared of death?
- Only those who love their lives..

39
00:05:12.380 --> 00:05:15.140
..are afraid of death. - Smart-aleck..

40
00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:25.140
Suraj! Don't be afraid!
I'm right here!

41
00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:26.540
I've got your clothes.

42
00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:44.020
They have swords
in their hands. Get in.

43
00:05:51.940 --> 00:05:53.860
Where have you been? - I went to..

44
00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:56.940
..make Madhav see reason. father.
- To make him see reason?

45
00:05:57.260 --> 00:06:00.620
And what did you finally do?
- What could I do. father..?

46
00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:03.060
Suraj wasn't the one..
who started the fight. brother.

47
00:06:03.140 --> 00:06:05.420
He raised his hands first and Suraj..

48
00:06:05.500 --> 00:06:07.260
Your indulgence has spoiled him.

49
00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:12.060
Why? Don't you love him?
You love him the most.

50
00:06:12.260 --> 00:06:16.260
That's exactly why I'm worried.
Don't ever mess with them again.

51
00:06:17.260 --> 00:06:19.260
Himmat is no small-time thug.

52
00:06:20.700 --> 00:06:25.140
Had something happened to you.
what would your father do?

53
00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:31.780
Suraj..? Balwant Singh's son? - Yes.

54
00:06:31.860 --> 00:06:32.940
Shut up!

55
00:06:33.340 --> 00:06:35.700
He has challenged Himmat's.

56
00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:39.860
I'll have his hands and feet broken..

57
00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:41.940
Cool it. dad.. - Damn you!

58
00:07:44.460 --> 00:07:45.580
Well. I..

59
00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:52.500
Doesn't my girl play
the piano so well?

60
00:07:55.340 --> 00:07:59.020
Why are you staring at her?
Do you recognise her?

61
00:07:59.940 --> 00:08:00.820
Sapna.

62
00:08:04.260 --> 00:08:05.340
You're Suraj. right?

63
00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:09.420
Nice introduction. I say.

64
00:08:09.660 --> 00:08:12.340
No one introduced the
two of you to each other.

65
00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:15.660
So how did you get to know each other?

66
00:08:15.860 --> 00:08:18.340
Aunt. father told us yesterday..

67
00:08:18.620 --> 00:08:20.740
..that his childhood friend
Uncle Cheema is arriving.

68
00:08:21.060 --> 00:08:23.340
She had to be his daughter Sapna.

69
00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:27.220
But how did you recognise her.
my child?

70
00:08:27.660 --> 00:08:30.620
Daddy often says
that his friend's..

71
00:08:30.860 --> 00:08:33.140
..family has a poet in its midst.

72
00:08:33.540 --> 00:08:37.540
I'm no poet. but I do
write a few lines now and then.

73
00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:38.980
Hello son!

74
00:08:39.180 --> 00:08:40.940
Suraj! How are you. son?

75
00:08:41.180 --> 00:08:45.700
Come. let's embrace..
that was very satisfying.

76
00:08:45.780 --> 00:08:49.620
Which way have you come in?
- It's him. We went to fetch him.

77
00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:51.540
The guests are already home and..

78
00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:52.940
..this chap was still at the station

79
00:08:53.540 --> 00:08:57.300
How was I to know that a girl
from Bhatinda would be so modern?

80
00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:00.540
There was this girl in a
Salwar Kameez looking here and there.

81
00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:03.540
I walked up to her and said. "Sapna?"

82
00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:05.860
And look at my luck
she was Sapna!

83
00:09:05.940 --> 00:09:09.300
It was Rachna and
you took it for Sapna.

84
00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:12.460
All right. Whatever it is.
I said. "Where's daddy?"

85
00:09:12.540 --> 00:09:14.620
She said.
"He's dead." I said. "In the train?"

86
00:09:14.780 --> 00:09:17.740
She said. "No. in the village."
And I sat down there.. mourning.

87
00:09:18.100 --> 00:09:21.100
And along came this gentlemen..
Mr Cheema.. upfront.

88
00:09:21.180 --> 00:09:23.540
Imagine.
Here I am mourning his death..

89
00:09:23.620 --> 00:09:25.660
..and he stands before me.
How shocking!

90
00:09:27.980 --> 00:09:30.540
Finish your drink.
We must have another.

91
00:09:30.620 --> 00:09:32.540
Before talking about my past..

92
00:09:32.620 --> 00:09:35.740
..do see that my grown
up daughter is right here.

93
00:09:35.820 --> 00:09:38.260
Have you no shame at all?

94
00:09:38.740 --> 00:09:41.940
She knows everything. Your
wife must have told her everything.

95
00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:43.540
Right. Sapna?

96
00:09:43.620 --> 00:09:45.220
But there is something
your Mummy hasn't told you about.

97
00:09:45.540 --> 00:09:48.660
I didn't know about it either.
I'll tell you now.

98
00:09:48.660 --> 00:09:51.860
No! Not another word! - See?

99
00:09:52.140 --> 00:09:54.940
It isn't only me.
Every man is like that.

100
00:09:56.780 --> 00:09:57.260
You too?

101
00:09:57.340 --> 00:09:58.620
Have your food. Have your food.

102
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:02.860
Cheema. it's fun to have you here.

103
00:10:03.180 --> 00:10:05.820
Stay over for some more days.
What's your hurry to leave?

104
00:10:06.180 --> 00:10:08.780
I want to stay.
too. but it's necessary..

105
00:10:08.860 --> 00:10:11.700
..for me to get there by next week.

106
00:10:11.900 --> 00:10:15.900
But Sapna will stay here.

107
00:10:16.540 --> 00:10:17.660
Yes.

108
00:10:17.740 --> 00:10:21.180
Getting her an admission in
the college is your responsibility.

109
00:10:21.740 --> 00:10:23.540
Rest assured. uncle.
She'll get the admission.

110
00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:24.460
Great!

111
00:10:25.340 --> 00:10:28.260
Suraj. get us another drink son.

112
00:10:29.500 --> 00:10:32.980
Balwant. it was very
nice meeting Suraj again.

113
00:10:33.380 --> 00:10:37.220
I'm glad you offered him shelter.

114
00:10:37.980 --> 00:10:40.180
Or he'd have forever
longed for his mother's love.

115
00:10:42.340 --> 00:10:45.580
Isn't Suraj really your son?

116
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:50.420
My child he was not born to us..

117
00:10:51.420 --> 00:10:54.900
..but he's no lesser than a son.

118
00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:59.940
He was just a child
when I adopted him.

119
00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:02.860
He came from a rich family..

120
00:11:03.860 --> 00:11:06.220
..and never got the
love of his mother.

121
00:11:06.540 --> 00:11:09.020
His mother always kept
him far away from herself.

122
00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:14.980
His entire childhood was
spent in lonely servants' quarters.

123
00:11:15.900 --> 00:11:19.540
He wondered why his mother
reserved all her love and affection..

124
00:11:19.620 --> 00:11:22.380
..only for his younger brother.

