leaving their sons.

229
00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:15.820
Suraj.

230
00:22:22.300 --> 00:22:26.980
My word! Fantastic!
- The smell of Bhatinda.

231
00:22:27.660 --> 00:22:33.620
Here you are. Eat this.
- Don't you wait for Suraj at dinner?

232
00:22:34.100 --> 00:22:38.380
Do you want us to starve? - You..

233
00:22:38.460 --> 00:22:40.180
Eat quietly.

234
00:22:41.140 --> 00:22:45.860
Suraj! At nine today?
- Suraj. nice to see you come.

235
00:22:46.100 --> 00:22:48.460
I'm told you've
composed a new couplet.

236
00:22:48.660 --> 00:22:52.980
So recite a couplet.
- Yes! In the forests!

237
00:22:53.060 --> 00:22:54.460
Shut up Jugnu! - Come on Suraj.

238
00:22:54.980 --> 00:23:00.060
Recite a poem. please.
- Go ahead. son. A nice lively one.

239
00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:02.820
To remind my friend
of his younger days.

240
00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:05.780
Any couplet will do.
but not one on booze. Please!

241
00:23:05.860 --> 00:23:07.140
Recite it. Suraj.

242
00:23:07.220 --> 00:23:08.220
Come on. Suraj.

243
00:23:09.140 --> 00:23:10.220
"I was so high on what.."

244
00:23:10.300 --> 00:23:12.180
..I had seen of her last evening.."

245
00:23:13.420 --> 00:23:16.140
"..that my eyes were offended
when sleep took over.."

246
00:23:16.220 --> 00:23:18.420
Fantastic! "I was so high on what.."

247
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:21.300
"..I had seen of her last evening.."

248
00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:23.820
"That my eyes were offended
when sleep took over.."

249
00:23:23.900 --> 00:23:25.740
Wow! Wow!

250
00:24:02.660 --> 00:24:06.620
"Love.."

251
00:24:06.700 --> 00:24:10.380
"Has happened on the sly.."

252
00:24:10.460 --> 00:24:14.260
"I've sworn it.."

253
00:24:14.340 --> 00:24:17.740
"Ever so secretly.."

254
00:24:17.820 --> 00:24:24.780
"On the sly.."

255
00:24:25.540 --> 00:24:33.220
"The world will never get wind.."

256
00:24:33.380 --> 00:24:40.740
"When we meet secretly.."

257
00:24:41.020 --> 00:24:44.740
"Love.."

258
00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:48.620
"Has happened on the sly.."

259
00:24:48.700 --> 00:24:52.220
"I've sworn it.."

260
00:24:52.460 --> 00:24:56.300
"Ever so secretly.."

261
00:25:21.740 --> 00:25:29.500
"We'll let our eyes
speak for our hearts.."

262
00:25:29.580 --> 00:25:37.180
"To our lips.
we shall not bring a word.."

263
00:25:37.260 --> 00:25:44.780
"Pining. loneliness.."

264
00:25:44.860 --> 00:25:52.300
"we'll together put up with.."

265
00:25:52.380 --> 00:25:59.740
"Desire gives me a beautiful grief.."

266
00:25:59.820 --> 00:26:07.020
"This grief I shall
bear secretly too."

267
00:26:37.060 --> 00:26:44.700
"Ever since I have seen you.
my love.."

268
00:26:44.780 --> 00:26:52.300
"I have turned a
poet at first sight.."

269
00:26:52.460 --> 00:27:00.020
"I have hidden you away.."

270
00:27:00.100 --> 00:27:07.500
"in my heart. in my eyes.."

271
00:27:07.580 --> 00:27:15.140
"Without you. I find peace nowhere.."

272
00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:22.620
"Such is the state
you have brought me to.."

273
00:27:22.700 --> 00:27:30.220
"Love has happened on the sly.."

274
00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:38.220
"I've sworn it ever so secretly.."

275
00:27:42.260 --> 00:27:47.340
She said that liquor is
evil and you gave up drinking!

276
00:27:48.300 --> 00:27:50.820
But I'm keeping you company. - No!

277
00:27:51.060 --> 00:27:52.820
Even if a drinker
stops going to the bar..

278
00:27:52.900 --> 00:27:55.380
..he never gives up drinking.

279
00:27:55.900 --> 00:28:00.420
Tell Sapna that you're
in love with her.

280
00:28:02.300 --> 00:28:06.300
Don't delay it anymore. my friend.
Make a booking at once.

281
00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:11.060
Or you might see her hooked elsewhere.

282
00:28:13.260 --> 00:28:15.260
Welcome sir.

283
00:28:18.940 --> 00:28:22.900
How much money?
- Bachelor? I'm married.

284
00:28:24.500 --> 00:28:29.500
So you're a bit hard of hearing?
- Hard up? It's 1300 rupees!

285
00:28:29.700 --> 00:28:34.220
1300 ? So little?
I'll give you 200 more. A tip.

286
00:28:34.300 --> 00:28:39.100
1500 makes nice hearing. right?
- 1500 ? One moment.

287
00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:50.640
Maybe it's in the other pocket.

288
00:28:55.520 --> 00:28:56.640
Maybe in the third.

289
00:29:03.640 --> 00:29:04.840
No pocket at all.

290
00:29:06.600 --> 00:29:09.480
Looks like my wallet has been picked.

291
00:29:15.200 --> 00:29:18.720
Look. mister.
I've started business only today..

292
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:22.879
and you're my first passenger.
So please skip these nasty jokes.

293
00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:25.720
I'll have a heart-attack
and you'll be..

294
00:29:25.799 --> 00:29:27.999
.. imprisoned for killing me. My fare.

295
00:29:28.319 --> 00:29:32.279
Strange man!
You're worried about your fare.

296
00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:35.160
I've been relieved
of 500 500-rupee notes.

297
00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:37.200
And you no sympathies at all.

298
00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:41.080
I think I have to show my
sympathy to him now. One moment.

299
00:29:41.160 --> 00:29:44.200
Friends. come here. come here.

300
00:29:45.360 --> 00:29:48.800
This man has lost his purse.
Show him some sympathy. please.

301
00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:51.720
He hasn't any money to pay the fare..

302
00:29:51.800 --> 00:29:54.040
..Show him some sympathy. please.

303
00:29:54.120 --> 00:29:58.560
How much was the fare. Jugnu?
- 1500 rupees.

304
00:29:58.640 --> 00:30:01.960
1000 was the fare.
200 was the tip.. - What tip?

305
00:30:02.040 --> 00:30:05.200
I don't have money to pay the fare..
- You yourself told me!

306
00:30:05.280 --> 00:30:10.240
He made me spend on cigarettes.
said he didn't have any change.

307
00:30:10.320 --> 00:30:12.840
And now he says the wallet is missing.
Beat him up!

308
00:30:12.920 --> 00:30:14.400
What kind of a person are you?

309
00:30:14.880 --> 00:30:17.720
It's just money..
- I'll not spare you.

310
00:30:17.800 --> 00:30:22.160
Wait.. how much money is it?
- You'll pay for him. Suraj?

311
00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:23.800
I've been watching the farce.

312
00:30:23.880 --> 00:30:25.280
Such a thing could happen to anyone.

313
00:30:25.360 --> 00:30:27.600
Don't you see?
He appears to come from a nice family.

314
00:30:27.680 --> 00:30:31.480
Right. big brother.
I really come from a decent family.

315
00:30:31.560 --> 00:30:36.120
Or I'd have paid him. I was
even carrying my credit cards in it.

316
00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:39.360
How much money. uncle? - 1500 rupees.

317
00:30:39.680 --> 00:30:44.800
1500 for what? Deduct 200 from it.
- All right. give me 1300.

318
00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:46.880
1500.

319
00:30:47.800 --> 00:30:48.600
Take this.

320
00:30:48.840 --> 00:30:51.200
I'll fix you. - What? What?

321
00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:57.400
Brother.. where are you going?
Give me your address. please.

322
00:30:57.760 --> 00:31:00.120
I've got to return your money.
- No. it's all right.

323
00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:04.160
Oh no. how's that possible.
I come from a respectable family.

324
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:07.200
Please give me your card.
I'll return your money to you.

325
00:31:07.280 --> 00:31:09.480
I promise. - Here.

326
00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:11.800
Thank you. Thank you for your help.

327
00:31:16.720 --> 00:31:22.160
Suraj Singh.
Partner. Gun Park Royal Hotel.

328
00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:24.320
Here's your money.

329
00:31:25.840 --> 00:31:28.400
Here's your salary for today.
You needn't come tomorrow.

330
00:31:28.480 --> 00:31:31.000
Why? - Suraj paid up today.

331
00:31:31.080 --> 00:31:32.040
Who's going to pay up tomorrow?

332
00:31:35.200 --> 00:31:36.480
Damn you!

333
00:31:36.640 --> 00:31:40.360
Raj Chauhan.. you must have
a booking in my name. - Sorry sir.

334
00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:43.040
There's no booking in your name.
- Are you sure?

335
00:31:43.200 --> 00:31:45.680
Where's that bloody Suraj..?
- Sir. excuse me.

336
00:31:46.040 --> 00:31:49.680
You're talking about our boss.
- Boss. he is to you.

337
00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:55.480
He's my childhood friend.
I'll give him such a tight slap.

338
00:31:55.800 --> 00:31:58.800
He begs me to come here and
doesn't even come to receive me.

339
00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:01.720
And there isn't even a room for me!
Isn't it wrong..?

340
00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:03.880
It is wrong sir.

341
00:32:03.960 --> 00:32:06.920
Mr Gupta.
looks like Mr Suraj forgot to tell..

342
00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:08.720
..us about his friend's arrival.

343
00:32:09.080 --> 00:32:13.120
But he has even given up drinking.
- Maybe that's why he forgot.

344
00:32:13.200 --> 00:32:13.760
Okay.

345
00:32:13.840 --> 00:32:17.240
If he goes away.
you might even lose your job. sir.

346
00:32:17.240 --> 00:32:17.760
If he goes away.
you might even lose your job. sir.
I'm leaving. This is an insult.
- Sir. sir. Excuse me. sir.

347
00:32:17.760 --> 00:32:19.720
I'm leaving. This is an insult.
- Sir. sir. Excuse me. sir.

348
00:32:20.480 --> 00:32:22.520
Didn't you talk about a room. sir?

349
00:32:22.600 --> 00:32:24.960
Actually there's a suite
booked in your name. sir.

350
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:27.120
Go and get it ready.

351
00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:29.800
I like that. I like that.
I like you. - Thank you sir.

352
00:32:29.880 --> 00:32:33.360
You hide your boss's weakness.
Nice employee.

353
00:32:33.520 --> 00:32:35.800
Thank you sir.
- All right. I'll take the suite.

354
00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:39.200
But don't tell Suraj I'm staying here

355
00:32:39.520 --> 00:32:42.560
No. - I want to see
when he thinks of me.

356
00:32:42.640 --> 00:32:43.480
Right sir.

357
00:32:44.040 --> 00:32:47.040
Don't shake your head.
For your father's sake. you mustn't.

358
00:32:51.220 --> 00:32:52.060
Sir.

359
00:32:53.660 --> 00:32:57.060
Looks like you forgot
to tell us about your friend.

360
00:32:57.340 --> 00:33:00.540
But I've given him a suite.
- My friend..?

361
00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:02.500
Raja..?

362
00:33:04.100 --> 00:33:09.140
Please don't tell him that
I've already reminded you. sir.

363
00:33:09.620 --> 00:33:11.580
He has implored me
in the name of my father.

364
00:33:12.660 --> 00:33:17.460
Implored you?
- My father's dead. sir..

365
00:33:17.540 --> 00:33:19.480
..won't make a difference
if I break my promise

366
00:33:19.480 --> 00:33:19.500
..won't make a difference
if I break my promise
All right.
The suite. isn't it? - Yes. sir.

367
00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:22.240
All right.
The suite. isn't it? - Yes. sir.

368
00:33:23.140 --> 00:33:24.300
Keep it. Keep it. Come in.

369
00:33:25.960 --> 00:33:27.480
The door won't open on the outside.

370
00:33:27.960 --> 00:33:29.840
Open it. You want me to open it then?

371
00:33:35.740 --> 00:33:36.940
I'll explain this. sir..

372
00:33:37.380 --> 00:33:39.460
..what are you guys watching?
Get going!

373
00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:42.300
Stay.. throw his stuff out.

374
00:33:43.140 --> 00:33:45.220
Let's sort it out between ourselves.

375
00:33:45.380 --> 00:33:48.740
I want them to see
how I deal with frauds.

376
00:33:48.820 --> 00:33:51.580
I was hungry. sir.
And I'm even willing to do the dishes.

377
00:33:51.660 --> 00:33:55.020
Really? Throw it out.
- What are you doing..?

378
00:33:55.180 --> 00:33:58.100
Don't have it thrown. sir.
- You throw it out then.

379
00:33:58.180 --> 00:33:59.660
I have stuff in it. sir. - Throw it!

380
00:34:01.100 --> 00:34:04.260
Was there anything else?
- My respect. sir. And you..

381
00:34:04.340 --> 00:34:06.740
Respect?
- I come from a nice family. sir.

382
00:34:06.820 --> 00:34:09.260
Nice family. eh? Rotten..

383
00:34:10.060 --> 00:34:12.940
Sorry sir. I got hurt in my eye.

384
00:34:13.540 --> 00:34:14.900
You. son?

385
00:34:14.980 --> 00:34:18.540
Uncle Rastogi! How are you? - Fine.

386
00:34:18.780 --> 00:34:20.580
Mr. Rastogi. do you know him?
- Of course.

387
00:34:20.660 --> 00:34:24.180
He's from a rich family in Jaipur.
He has a huge bungalow there.

388
00:34:24.260 --> 00:34:26.900
Yes. tell them.
- Are you here on a vacation. son?

389
00:34:27.260 --> 00:34:30.020
If someone lets me have a vacation.

390
00:34:30.100 --> 00:34:35.340
The hills are very beautiful.
- And dangerous too.

391
00:34:35.540 --> 00:34:38.380
Enjoy yourself. young man.
Enjoy yourself. - Bye.

392
00:34:38.820 --> 00:34:39.860
Hear that?

393
00:34:41.340 --> 00:34:43.180
Come on in. You may go.

394
00:34:44.380 --> 00:34:47.740
Excuse me. With or without luggage?

395
00:34:48.060 --> 00:34:49.300
Bring it all in.

396
00:34:50.300 --> 00:34:51.360
Thank you.

397
00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:51.380
Thank you.
Now look. Maybe you come from
a decent family.. - Big brother..

398
00:34:51.380 --> 00:34:54.280
Now look. Maybe you come from
a decent family.. - Big brother..

399
00:34:55.880 --> 00:34:56.600
Got hurt.

400
00:34:57.320 --> 00:35:01.600
You've always come to my
rescue like an elder brother.

401
00:35:02.560 --> 00:35:07.040
May I call you Big Brother?
- Certainly.

402
00:35:07.280 --> 00:35:08.320
Thank you. thank you.

403
00:35:08.760 --> 00:35:12.360
The problem is.
mother's forcing me into a marriage.

404
00:35:12.440 --> 00:35:16.000
And there's someone else I love.
- Where is the girl?

405
00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:19.960
I don't know.
but I'm told she's in this very city.

406
00:35:20.280 --> 00:35:24.040
Big Brother. in just one glimpse..

407
00:35:25.240 --> 00:35:29.000
..I gave my heart away to her.

408
00:35:37.320 --> 00:35:40.600
You saw her at the fashion show.
You must've taken pictures too?

409
00:35:42.120 --> 00:35:46.480
If only I could gather my wits.
I'd surely have taken pictures.

410
00:35:47.760 --> 00:35:49.520
I was blown out.

411
00:35:52.920 --> 00:35:55.920
Strange. isn't it?
But this is how matters..

412
00:35:56.640 --> 00:36:00.440
..of the heart are. Big Brother.

413
00:36:12.380 --> 00:36:13.820
Deep in thought. eh?

414
00:36:14.420 --> 00:36:17.300
From the look of it.
you are in love with someone too.

415
00:36:17.900 --> 00:36:19.460
I was thinking what a fool you are.

416
00:36:19.860 --> 00:36:21.020
You don't know where the girl lives..

417
00:36:21.100 --> 00:36:23.220
..and you're out to find her.
How will you?

418
00:36:23.420 --> 00:36:26.940
With your help. If you help me..

419
00:36:27.020 --> 00:36:29.460
..my work will be done. Big Brother.

420
00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:31.900
It has to do with love.. okay?

421
00:36:33.180 --> 00:36:35.900
What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

422
00:36:35.980 --> 00:36:40.140
What a look you cast at my taxi
I had to close down that business..

423
00:36:40.220 --> 00:36:44.740
..and I start a canteen here.
- Here? I see.

424
00:36:44.820 --> 00:36:47.860
You've followed me.
here to torment me.

425
00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:50.020
Who gave you my whereabouts?

426
00:36:50.100 --> 00:36:52.180
Why did you come into
my life again? Why..?

427
00:36:52.260 --> 00:36:54.020
What harm have I done to you?

428
00:36:54.100 --> 00:36:57.060
You're the one who
came into my life. - Me..?

429
00:36:57.140 --> 00:36:57.940
Yes.

430
00:36:59.220 --> 00:37:01.460
We weren't related in
our previous birth. were we?

431
00:37:01.900 --> 00:37:03.980
We aren't brothers
lost in the fair. are we?

432
00:37:04.060 --> 00:37:08.860
There! You spoke my heart!

433
00:37:09.180 --> 00:37:11.700
Brother! My brother!

434
00:37:12.500 --> 00:37:13.540
My brother!

435
00:37:14.900 --> 00:37:19.020
If we are brothers.
we ought to help each other. Right?

436
00:37:19.140 --> 00:37:21.140
Who's doing what to whom? - You.

437
00:37:21.220 --> 00:37:23.060
What..? - Help me.

438
00:37:24.340 --> 00:37:27.500
All right.
Which girl are you here to bother?

439
00:37:31.980 --> 00:37:34.500
How did you know I'm
here to bother a girl?

440
00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:38.820
It shows on your face.
- I looked tired. don't I?

441
00:37:39.460 --> 00:37:43.060
Just two women's colleges in the city.
One. I've checked out.

442
00:37:43.140 --> 00:37:46.860
She ought to be here then. right?
- Yes. Exactly!

443
00:37:47.620 --> 00:37:50.900
She must be here.
Find her. And tease her!

444
00:37:50.980 --> 00:37:56.980
But please let me run my canteen!
Let me sell my snacks!

445
00:37:57.620 --> 00:37:58.380
Listen.

446
00:38:01.580 --> 00:38:02.580
What luck man!

447
00:38:02.660 --> 00:38:04.420
So you told her. right?

448
00:38:05.140 --> 00:38:06.100
Hi.

449
00:38:06.180 --> 00:38:07.620
He is calling you.
isn't he? - Hi.

450
00:38:08.620 --> 00:38:12.060
Hi Sapna.
Haven't you recognized me? - No

451
00:38:12.140 --> 00:38:15.100
That's strange. Everything's
fine back home in Bhatinda. I hope?

452
00:38:15.660 --> 00:38:18.300
Yes. but I haven't..
- You don't recognize me. right?

453
00:38:19.060 --> 00:38:22.900
How would you?
We were never introduced.

454
00:38:23.660 --> 00:38:26.180
I saw you at the fashion
show - Who is he?

455
00:38:26.260 --> 00:38:28.900
You're the one I've
been looking for ever since.

456
00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:32.700
When I set out from home.
I was carrying 200.000 rupees.

457
00:38:32.780 --> 00:38:37.140
And now. I have nothing.
- You want to borrow money from her?

458
00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:38.660
Don't be silly.

459
00:38:38.740 --> 00:38:41.780
I only wanted to tell her
that I can do anything for her.

460
00:38:41.860 --> 00:38:44.780
Really? Anything? - Of course.

461
00:38:44.860 --> 00:38:48.060
I can even die for her.
- No. don't die for her.

462
00:38:48.140 --> 00:38:49.900
Or she'll be arrested.

463
00:38:50.060 --> 00:38:51.140
Very funny.

464
00:38:51.660 --> 00:38:53.660
So you can do anything for me?
- Of course.

465
00:38:54.540 --> 00:38:55.740
See that man?

466
00:38:56.380 --> 00:38:56.940
Good morning. sir.

467
00:38:57.020 --> 00:38:59.380
Good morning. How
are you. students?

468
00:38:59.460 --> 00:39:01.100
Just get me his hat.

469
00:39:01.200 --> 00:39:03.960
You think you can't? - No.

470
00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:07.720
I was thinking what
a trivia you asked me to do.

471
00:39:07.800 --> 00:39:12.040
His hat. isn't it?
Not his trousers. I hope.

472
00:39:12.120 --> 00:39:14.000
I'll get it. Uncle.

473
00:39:14.080 --> 00:39:16.200
The principal isn't sparing him.

474
00:39:17.400 --> 00:39:19.680
Our college is participating
in the dance-competition too.

475
00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:21.160
Okay? Happy?

476
00:39:23.160 --> 00:39:24.480
Be prepared.

477
00:39:26.840 --> 00:39:28.200
Don't be nervous. - Hello. Uncle.

478
00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:31.600
Hello. You're wearing a nice hat.
Will you give it to me?

479
00:39:31.840 --> 00:39:32.440
What?

480
00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:34.480
Hello aunty. - Aunty?

481
00:39:34.720 --> 00:39:36.080
What is this nonsense. Catch him!

482
00:39:36.640 --> 00:39:38.320
Let go..

483
00:39:38.760 --> 00:39:39.640
Sapna! - Call the police.

484
00:39:44.280 --> 00:39:47.240
There was a call from the police
station. They've arrested some boy.

485
00:39:47.880 --> 00:39:52.560
What have I to do with him?
- He says you're his elder brother.

486
00:39:52.640 --> 00:39:54.200
He's even carrying your business card.

487
00:39:55.480 --> 00:39:57.560
Why did I give that lover-boy my card?

488
00:40:01.340 --> 00:40:03.220
Please pack this. - Yes. go ahead.

489
00:40:03.300 --> 00:40:08.900
And.. - Aunt. you said Suraj never
helped out with domestic affairs.

490
00:40:08.980 --> 00:40:11.500
But look at him.
He's even choosing jewellery.

491
00:40:12.140 --> 00:40:15.220
Oh yes! There's a sea change in Suraj.

492
00:40:15.300 --> 00:40:18.700
And why..?
Only he knows. Show me that one.

493
00:40:18.780 --> 00:40:20.580
How's this one?
- How much is it worth?

494
00:40:20.660 --> 00:40:25.660
Sapna. buy some jewellery
for yourself. - Yes. Sapna. Go ahead.

495
00:40:26.020 --> 00:40:28.780
No. I'm not fond of jeweler.

496
00:40:28.860 --> 00:40:31.180
But you will wear some very soon.

497
00:40:31.260 --> 00:40:34.460
If you don't make a choice.
someone will choose for you. Right?

498
00:40:34.700 --> 00:40:36.300
Aunty. you..

499
00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:49.000
Lovely necklace.
Whom are you buying it for?

500
00:40:50.560 --> 00:40:53.040
For you. - What?

501
00:40:54.440 --> 00:40:56.080
Try it on.

502
00:40:58.160 --> 00:40:59.280
Put it around my neck.

503
00:41:13.120 --> 00:41:18.400
Wow! How does it look?
- It looks beautiful now.

504
00:41:22.400 --> 00:41:23.640
Mr Suraj..

505
00:41:26.920 --> 00:41:28.240
Mr Suraj..

506
00:41:31.760 --> 00:41:35.720
Want me to pack this? - Put this away.

507
00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:37.520
I'll pick it up later.

508
00:41:39.080 --> 00:41:42.280
What will you have? - Pepsi

509
00:41:42.720 --> 00:41:44.280
You? - Pepsi?

510
00:41:44.680 --> 00:41:47.880
Really? I'll have a coffee.

511
00:41:54.280 --> 00:42:00.400
This boy's been bothering
me for so many days. Take a look..

512
00:42:01.520 --> 00:42:02.360
Oh God!

513
00:42:04.400 --> 00:42:07.240
Want me to fix him..? Wait a moment.

514
00:42:10.120 --> 00:42:16.760
So spoilt brat!
She's the girl. isn't she?

515
00:42:16.840 --> 00:42:20.040
You will tease our girl. will you?

516
00:42:21.600 --> 00:42:23.480
Your girl? - Yes.

517
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:26.800
She neither looks like you.
nor behaves like you.

518
00:42:27.760 --> 00:42:30.040
And who's the one who
has gone away to Canada?

519
00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:33.600
So you've made all enquiries!

520
00:42:33.880 --> 00:42:36.960
Even if she's his daughter.
she's our responsibility!

521
00:42:37.320 --> 00:42:42.720
You will tease our girl..? - Uncle!

522
00:42:42.960 --> 00:42:46.120
Why're you folding your trousers?
- It's easier to run away.

523
00:42:46.200 --> 00:42:49.840
How do you know?
Only those who are guilty. run away!

524
00:42:49.920 --> 00:42:52.640
I'm not sparing you!
- And I'm not letting go of her.

525
00:42:52.720 --> 00:42:54.880
So you're challenging me! - Sure.

526
00:42:54.960 --> 00:42:57.200
All right. I'll deal with you! - Ok.

527
00:43:20.360 --> 00:43:30.200
"Love.."

528
00:43:34.640 --> 00:43:39.440
"Come into my life. my love"

529
00:43:39.520 --> 00:43:44.120
"Bring fragrance to
my life with your love"

530
00:43:44.200 --> 00:43:48.840
"Come into my life. my love"

531
00:43:48.920 --> 00:43:53.000
"Never leave my life ever"

532
00:43:53.080 --> 00:44:02.560
"Love.."

533
00:44:02.640 --> 00:44:12.560
"Love.."

534
00:44:30.560 --> 00:44:34.600
"Your beauty torments me all night"

535
00:44:34.760 --> 00:44:39.280
"You are the one
I dream of all the time"

536
00:44:39.800 --> 00:44:44.000
"It isn't easy to trap
me with your sweet words"

537
00:44:44.080 --> 00:44:48.720
"I'm no butterfly anyone
can lay his hands on"

538
00:44:49.160 --> 00:44:58.360
"Love.."

539
00:44:58.600 --> 00:45:07.000
"Love.."

540
00:45:33.300 --> 00:45:37.220
"My love is meant for the one.."

541
00:45:37.300 --> 00:45:41.900
"who will belong to
me through seven lifetimes"

542
00:45:42.060 --> 00:45:46.540
"So much of love I have
for you in my heart. my love.."

543
00:45:46.820 --> 00:45:51.500
"even a hundred lifetimes won't
be enough to give it all to you"

544
00:45:59.460 --> 00:46:08.540
"Love.."

545
00:46:14.100 --> 00:46:15.180
What am I to do with you?

546
00:46:17.260 --> 00:46:19.940
Please arrange for my bail.
Big Brother.

547
00:46:20.420 --> 00:46:23.420
So you'll land behind bars again?
Do you like it there?

548
00:46:23.500 --> 00:46:26.980
Not at all.
I'm the first man in my family..

549
00:46:27.740 --> 00:46:29.620
..to ever have been behind bars.

550
00:46:31.060 --> 00:46:34.100
Introduce me to the girl.

551
00:46:34.180 --> 00:46:35.300
I'll talk to her on your behalf.

552
00:46:35.380 --> 00:46:37.340
Let me at least bring
her around first.

553
00:46:37.580 --> 00:46:41.380
I'll introduce you afterwards.
- Khan. please forgive this lover.

554
00:46:41.740 --> 00:46:44.140
I'll come this evening
to sign the bail papers.

555
00:46:44.220 --> 00:46:45.140
Okay.

556
00:46:48.280 --> 00:46:51.160
Say a proper job.
I've found a new job. - Yes.

557
00:46:51.360 --> 00:46:53.760
"Hail divine Mother.."

558
00:46:53.840 --> 00:46:56.200
Softly.. I can hear you.

559
00:46:57.200 --> 00:47:02.240
What's the prayer for. uncle?
- As my mother said..

560
00:47:03.000 --> 00:47:05.520
when there is no way.
set out on one path.

561
00:47:05.760 --> 00:47:07.280
You will find your goal.

562
00:47:07.760 --> 00:47:11.600
But you know what your goal is.
A job.. and the sack.

563
00:47:11.800 --> 00:47:18.200
So what's the prayer for?
- To make money! Lots of money!

564
00:47:18.680 --> 00:47:21.760
Money? What for?
- I've got to get two guys bumped off.

565
00:47:22.400 --> 00:47:26.560
Which two guys?
- One. I can do nothing about.

566
00:47:26.640 --> 00:47:29.200
The other is the guy who bails
this chap out. when he's arrested.

567
00:47:29.200 --> 00:47:30.000
The other is the guy who bails
this chap out. when he's arrested.
Who's it?
- That vagabond. that loafer!

568
00:47:30.000 --> 00:47:32.360
Who's it?
- That vagabond. that loafer!

569
00:47:32.440 --> 00:47:37.760
Who teases Sapna at the college.
- Who is he?

570
00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:40.560
He's the one you
paid the taxi fare for.

571
00:47:40.640 --> 00:47:42.440
That fraud who claims
to come from a decent family.

572
00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:44.840
He has made life miserable for Sapna.

573
00:47:45.040 --> 00:47:47.760
She won't even look at him..

574
00:47:47.840 --> 00:47:51.400
..and this shameless chap
won't stop bothering her!

575
00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:53.880
Gupta. where is Raja? - Sir..

576
00:47:53.960 --> 00:47:54.960
Where's Raja?

577
00:47:55.280 --> 00:47:55.960
You..?

578
00:47:56.220 --> 00:47:58.860
Why are you here?
Want to get me kicked out of here too?

579
00:47:58.940 --> 00:48:02.260
Go away! - No Jugnu.

580
00:48:02.340 --> 00:48:08.620
I just want Sapna's address.
- Why? To go and flirt with her?

581
00:48:08.700 --> 00:48:10.420
Try doing that!
- You're taking me wrong.

582
00:48:10.500 --> 00:48:12.660
Not to flirt. I want to make her mine.

583
00:48:13.580 --> 00:48:15.020
I belong to an aristocratic family.

584
00:48:15.100 --> 00:48:17.980
Really? - Give me her address.
I swear..

585
00:48:18.060 --> 00:48:20.340
I'll see to it that your
job gets confirmed in my company.

586
00:48:20.420 --> 00:48:22.260
Really? Now look mister..

587
00:48:22.340 --> 00:48:24.460
..if you belong to an
aristocratic family. I'm no less.

588
00:48:24.540 --> 00:48:27.100
I wouldn't stoop so low for a job.
- Listen.

589
00:48:27.180 --> 00:48:30.140
Nonsense!
- You're misunderstanding me.

590
00:48:30.220 --> 00:48:33.020
Now go away. Else.
you'll see the worst of me.

591
00:48:33.100 --> 00:48:36.340
Please. try to understand..
- Please! Go away!

592
00:48:36.420 --> 00:48:37.140
Big brother..?

593
00:48:38.460 --> 00:48:39.620
What's the matter. big brother?

594
00:48:40.500 --> 00:48:41.940
Big brother? Stop that farce!

595
00:48:42.660 --> 00:48:46.020
Sapna belongs to a respectable family.
And she is my guest.

596
00:48:46.500 --> 00:48:49.340
If you even set your
sights on her again..

597
00:48:53.340 --> 00:48:54.420
I'll kill you!

598
00:48:56.020 --> 00:48:59.380
I'm sorry big brother.
I can't promise.

599
00:49:05.380 --> 00:49:07.180
You will flirt with her. will you?

600
00:49:08.020 --> 00:49:10.700
Big brother. I respect you a lot.

601
00:49:11.380 --> 00:49:14.580
But I love Sapna lot
more than I respect you.

602
00:49:21.540 --> 00:49:22.980
You want to seduce her!
And you say you love her?

603
00:49:27.220 --> 00:49:30.380
Who do you think you are?
I'm no cheapskate.

604
00:49:31.340 --> 00:49:32.340
I'm Raghuveer Singh Chauhan's son.

605
00:49:32.420 --> 00:49:33.860
The only heir to Raghuveer Industries.

606
00:49:33.940 --> 00:49:34.900
Liar!

607
00:49:36.540 --> 00:49:38.020
I'm not lying. big brother.

608
00:49:38.620 --> 00:49:42.180
The Rajput mansion
in this city belongs to me.

609
00:49:42.380 --> 00:49:45.580
Lying again?
It belongs to Savitri Devi

610
00:49:52.460 --> 00:49:55.820
Savitri Devi is my mother.

611
00:49:57.220 --> 00:50:01.220
Now you'll say that I'm lying.
Let me ask you something

612
00:50:01.900 --> 00:50:04.740
Can you prove that your
mother is really your mother?

613
00:50:05.580 --> 00:50:06.300
Answer me.

614
00:50:08.420 --> 00:50:09.540
Tell me.

615
00:50:47.620 --> 00:50:49.380
I'm leaving your hotel.

616
00:50:51.460 --> 00:50:53.100
Not this city.

617
00:50:53.940 --> 00:50:59.460
Do what you want.
But I'm not going away from Sapna.

618
00:51:03.140 --> 00:51:05.420
Just what I wanted to hear from you.

619
00:51:06.060 --> 00:51:08.620
I wanted to know
how much you love her.

620
00:51:09.420 --> 00:51:13.460
I now believe. you love her dearly.

621
00:51:15.380 --> 00:51:20.460
By the way. I trusted you.
but deep inside. I suspected.

622
00:51:21.220 --> 00:51:27.140
That's why I had to put you to test.
Forgive me. Raja.

623
00:51:28.620 --> 00:51:29.380
Raja.

624
00:51:30.500 --> 00:51:31.420
I'm sorry.

625
00:51:38.180 --> 00:51:38.900
Sure.

626
00:51:51.260 --> 00:51:54.700
Frankly speaking big brother.
you are an enigma.

627
00:51:55.660 --> 00:51:57.660
I don't understand you either.

628
00:51:58.060 --> 00:51:59.300
You left mother behind..

629
00:51:59.380 --> 00:52:02.340
I mean how could you
leave your mother and come here?

630
00:52:03.100 --> 00:52:04.460
Who will take care of her?

631
00:52:08.020 --> 00:52:13.140
Point. Everything was
fine while Daddy was alive.

632
00:52:14.460 --> 00:52:16.420
He passed away four years ago.

633
00:52:21.260 --> 00:52:26.300
Ever since. I never left mother alone.

634
00:52:27.340 --> 00:52:31.940
But I couldn't help it.
She was after me to get married.

635
00:52:32.020 --> 00:52:34.980
Had I not run away.
I'd have been married by now.

636
00:52:36.060 --> 00:52:38.900
Think big brother.
What would've happened to Sapna?

637
00:52:39.660 --> 00:52:41.380
Who would've married her?

638
00:52:43.100 --> 00:52:44.860
Just okay.

639
00:52:45.700 --> 00:52:49.780
Thousands might be
dreaming about marrying her.

640
00:52:52.780 --> 00:52:55.780
But I dream of her everyday.

641
00:52:56.780 --> 00:53:01.540
I fear. should my dream shatter.
how will I survive?

642
00:53:02.940 --> 00:53:04.260
If I could get one picture of her..

643
00:53:04.340 --> 00:53:08.900
Why don't you introduce her to mother?

644
00:53:09.140 --> 00:53:10.500
You're strange. big brother.

645
00:53:10.740 --> 00:53:12.500
I haven't yet been
introduced to her properly.

646
00:53:12.580 --> 00:53:13.900
And you ask me to
introduce her to mother?

647
00:53:14.700 --> 00:53:17.540
I don't even know if she likes me.

648
00:53:17.900 --> 00:53:20.860
What if she refuses to meet mother?
- She won't.

649
00:53:21.660 --> 00:53:26.620
Not consolation. I need your help.
Just help me once. please.

650
00:53:26.820 --> 00:53:30.340
She lives in your house.
she heeds you too.

651
00:53:30.420 --> 00:53:32.700
Tell her that I'm a gentleman.

652
00:53:33.460 --> 00:53:37.100
That might just hit home.
Please. - I'll talk to her.

653
00:53:37.460 --> 00:53:40.660
Thank you. Thank you big brother.
thank you very much.

654
00:53:40.740 --> 00:53:44.740
Listen.. call mother over. quickly.
- Right away.

655
00:53:53.340 --> 00:53:56.940
Hello. - Hello mother? Raja here.

656
00:53:57.340 --> 00:54:01.660
Raja! Hopeless idiot!

657
00:54:01.740 --> 00:54:04.060
Ass! Fraud! Where have you been?

658
00:54:05.380 --> 00:54:08.180
For all these days of not
keeping in touch. she's blessing me.

659
00:54:08.300 --> 00:54:10.980
How long will you pursue that girl?
- Mother.

660
00:54:11.900 --> 00:54:13.900
I'm here only to meet her. Mother

661
00:54:13.980 --> 00:54:17.820
Yes. I've met her.
Come over at once. mother.

662
00:54:17.900 --> 00:54:19.180
I want to introduce her to you.

663
00:54:19.260 --> 00:54:21.460
Ass! Where are you? - What?

664
00:54:21.540 --> 00:54:25.860
Where are you?
- In Dharampur. I'm staying in a hotel

665
00:54:25.940 --> 00:54:27.580
We got such a huge
ancestral mansion there.

666
00:54:27.660 --> 00:54:28.740
And you're staying in a hotel?

667
00:54:28.980 --> 00:54:32.420
Ma. how can I stay
alone in that huge mansion?

668
00:54:32.500 --> 00:54:33.860
You haven't a cent on you.

669
00:54:33.940 --> 00:54:36.100
How could you stay
in a hotel all these days?

670
00:54:36.380 --> 00:54:40.820
Ma. I've found a brother..
a brother. in fact.

671
00:54:41.060 --> 00:54:44.260
I lovingly call him big brother.

672
00:54:45.140 --> 00:54:50.140
He's been so kind. One minute.
talk to him.. please talk to him.

673
00:54:53.460 --> 00:54:54.220
Hello.

674
00:54:54.620 --> 00:54:57.700
Hello son. - Mother..

675
00:54:58.780 --> 00:55:02.260
..you're coming. aren't you?
- I'll be coming come over. soon.

676
00:55:02.340 --> 00:55:06.500
Son. do you know the
girl Raja is talking about?

677
00:55:07.380 --> 00:55:08.420
Hello.

678
00:55:10.220 --> 00:55:11.420
Hello.

679
00:55:11.780 --> 00:55:18.780
Son. are you listening?
I said.. - Yes mother. I know her.

680
00:55:18.860 --> 00:55:21.180
She's very nice.

681
00:55:23.900 --> 00:55:26.060
Mother. come over quickly.

682
00:55:26.259 --> 00:55:28.019
Okay darling.

683
00:55:28.100 --> 00:55:29.700
Bye. - Okay bye.

684
00:55:30.900 --> 00:55:34.020
What's the matter. big brother?
You're in tears?

685
00:55:34.980 --> 00:55:37.940
What happened. brother?
- I talked to mother..

686
00:55:38.940 --> 00:55:40.420
Just couldn't help the tears.

687
00:56:05.380 --> 00:56:09.300
Sapna..? You haven't gone to bed yet?

688
00:56:13.180 --> 00:56:14.740
You broke the promise you gave me.
didn't you?

689
00:56:16.060 --> 00:56:17.340
You've broken our friendship.

690
00:56:23.460 --> 00:56:25.100
I haven't broken our friendship.

691
00:56:27.060 --> 00:56:32.860
You are still my friend.
and you will always be.

692
00:56:33.380 --> 00:56:37.420
But yes. I broke the promise. - Why?

693
00:56:40.780 --> 00:56:44.740
Tell me something?
Have you ever been in love?

694
00:56:45.940 --> 00:56:47.140
What kind of a question is that?

695
00:56:49.580 --> 00:56:51.820
Simple and clear.

696
00:56:52.860 --> 00:56:58.220
Have you ever loved someone.
like crazy?

697
00:56:59.620 --> 00:57:00.300
Love..?

698
00:57:05.980 --> 00:57:07.180
Know what Sapna?

699
00:57:09.140 --> 00:57:14.340
Love is strange.

700
00:57:16.340 --> 00:57:20.340
It is the essence
of all relationships.

701
00:57:22.060 --> 00:57:26.060
Those who have someone to
love them are indeed very fortunate.

702
00:57:28.340 --> 00:57:31.220
And you are one of them.

703
00:57:32.740 --> 00:57:37.060
Me..? Who loves me? - Raja.

704
00:57:38.740 --> 00:57:39.460
Raja.

705
00:57:41.060 --> 00:57:45.700
You've see only his pranks.
I know his feelings.

706
00:57:46.220 --> 00:57:50.020
He loves you.. dearly.

707
00:57:52.660 --> 00:57:59.580
If someone's love isn't requited.
he feels suffocated.

708
00:58:00.740 --> 00:58:02.100
Life becomes miserable.

709
00:58:03.620 --> 00:58:07.820
You seem to have
changed overnight. Suraj.

710
00:58:10.140 --> 00:58:14.220
Don't try to digress. Sapna.

711
00:58:15.060 --> 00:58:18.820
Give it a good thought.

712
00:58:19.980 --> 00:58:23.860
Raja is a nice boy.

713
00:58:24.780 --> 00:58:28.420
And he's madly in love with you.

714
00:58:29.660 --> 00:58:30.900
He loves you dearly.

715
00:58:39.300 --> 00:58:42.340
Winning a girl's
heart is as much a..

716
00:58:42.420 --> 00:58:44.180
..difficult task as it is easy. Raja.

717
00:58:44.700 --> 00:58:49.420
She could flip in a moment.
She could even take months to decide.

718
00:58:50.020 --> 00:58:54.380
And you have very little time.
- Big brother. flirting is fine.

719
00:58:54.540 --> 00:58:57.860
But I never imagined I'll
have to sing your couplets.

720
00:58:58.900 --> 00:59:01.340
What's the problem?
I'm with you. Sing it.

721
00:59:01.700 --> 00:59:03.740
No. You will teach me. - I..?

722
00:59:03.820 --> 00:59:04.340
Yes.

723
00:59:06.060 --> 00:59:06.900
All right.

724
01:00:06.300 --> 01:00:10.540
"You are my beloved"

725
01:00:10.820 --> 01:00:14.540
"You are the fragrance in the air"

726
01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:18.500
"Every moment.."

727
01:00:19.260 --> 01:00:22.540
"I think of you"

728
01:00:24.180 --> 01:00:28.620
"You are my beloved"

729
01:00:28.940 --> 01:00:32.540
"You are the fragrance in the air"

730
01:00:32.700 --> 01:00:36.580
"Every moment.."

731
01:00:37.340 --> 01:00:41.260
"I think of you"

732
01:00:41.280 --> 01:00:45.320
"Without seeing you. I swear.."

733
01:00:45.600 --> 01:00:49.640
"I can't breathe"

734
01:00:50.120 --> 01:00:56.760
"My heart's bound in a spell.."

735
01:00:58.120 --> 01:01:01.680
"that your love has cast"

736
01:01:02.560 --> 01:01:06.760
"that your love has cast"

737
01:01:07.480 --> 01:01:11.760
"You are my beloved"

738
01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:15.720
"You are the fragrance in the air"

739
01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:20.120
"Every moment.."

740
01:01:20.520 --> 01:01:24.640
"I think of you"

741
